	<p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><i><b>Pete 'n' Tillie</b></i> is a 1972 American comedy-drama film starring <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Walter_Matthau" title="Walter Matthau">Walter Matthau</a> and <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carol_Burnett" title="Carol Burnett">Carol Burnett</a> in the title roles. Its advertising tagline was "Honeymoon's over. It's time to get married."</p>
	<h2 xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <span class="mw-headline" id="Plot">Plot</span></h2>
	<p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Pete (Mathau) and Tillie (Burnett) marry, have a child and have their marriage tested by the child's death (<a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lee_Montgomery" title="Lee Montgomery">Lee Montgomery</a>).</p>
	<h2 xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <span class="mw-headline" id="Awards_and_nominations">Awards and nominations</span></h2>
	<p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">It was nominated for two <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Academy_Award" title="Academy Award">Academy Awards</a>, <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Julius_J._Epstein" title="Julius J. Epstein">Julius J. Epstein</a> for <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Academy_Award_for_Writing_Adapted_Screenplay" title="Academy Award for Writing Adapted Screenplay">Adapted Screenplay</a> and <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Geraldine_Page" title="Geraldine Page">Geraldine Page</a> for <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Academy_Award_for_Best_Supporting_Actress" title="Academy Award for Best Supporting Actress">Supporting Actress</a>.</p>
	<p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Walter Matthau won the 1973 <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BAFTA_Award_for_Best_Actor_in_a_Leading_Role" title="BAFTA Award for Best Actor in a Leading Role">BAFTA Award for Best Actor in a Leading Role</a> for this and for <i><a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Charley_Varrick" title="Charley Varrick">Charley Varrick</a></i></p>
	<h2 xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <span class="mw-headline" id="Cast">Cast</span></h2>
